Campaign_KPIs


1. Add-To-Cart % = 
DIVIDE(
    SUM(Additional_Information[Add_to_Cart]),
    SUM(Additional_Information[Clicks])
) //  To understand how many attends were made intended to buy the products after showing interest.
_________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

2. Cart Conversion Rate % = 
DIVIDE(
    DISTINCTCOUNT(Combined_Sales_Data_[Order_ID]),
 SUM(Additional_Information[Add_to_Cart]) 
) //  To understand how many orders did the product receive from a particular campaign.

_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

3. Click-Through-% = 
DIVIDE(
    SUM(Additional_Information[Clicks]),
    SUM(Additional_Information[Impression])
) // How many customers really showed interest in the products after viewing it.

_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

4. Conversion % = 
DIVIDE(DISTINCTCOUNT(Combined_Sales_Data_[Order_ID]),SUM(Additional_Information[Clicks])) // Rate of sales made sale by the campaign

________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

5. Campaign Budget = 
CALCULATE(
SUM(Additional_Information[Budget]),
CROSSFILTER(Additional_Information[Campaign],Campaign[Campaign],Both)
)
// How much is spent on campaign

____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

6. Customer Aquisition Cost = 
[Campaign Budget]/[Unit Sold] // Shows how the campaing the helps in acquiring customers
____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

7. Total CPC = 
DIVIDE([Campaign Budget],SUM(Additional_Information[Clicks])) // This shows how much has been spent on add, which determines the relevance of the campaign

__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

8. Return on Ad Spend% = 
([Total Sales]/[Campaign Budget]) // Sales made by the campaign

